            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fine egg noodles</strong> to a pot and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 1-2 min or until tender, then drain, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p><p>Once drained, return the noodles to the pot and set aside</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1611659987912-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1611659987912-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1611659987912-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1611659987912-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1611659987912-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lean beef has crisped, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the<strong> red chilli relish</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of your<strong> soy sauce</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!) and cook for a further 4 min or until everything is browned, crispy and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>lean</strong> <strong>crispy chilli beef</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1611659998378-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1611659998378-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1611659998378-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1611659998378-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1611659998378-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pot of <strong>drained noodles</strong> to a medium heat</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped spring onion </strong>and <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> to the pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and stir together until fully combined</p><p>Tip: Add a small splash of starchy noodle water if you need to loosen the noodles</p><p>Once combined, remove the pan from the heat and add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> – these are your <strong>coriander noodles</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1611660021307-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1611660021307-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1611660021307-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1611660021307-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1611660021307-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> lean crispy chilli beef</strong> over the <strong>coriander noodles</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> and <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
